---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Naman Chetwani"
  description="Personal website for Naman Chetwani."
>
  <main class="page">
    <div class="page-top">
      <nav class="top-nav" aria-label="Primary">
        <a class="nav-link current" href="/">Naman Chetwani</a>
        <a class="nav-link" href="/about">About</a>
        <a class="nav-link" href="/things-ive-done">Things I've Done</a>
        <a class="nav-link" href="/reading">Reading</a>
      </nav>
      <button class="theme-toggle" type="button" data-theme-toggle aria-label="Switch theme">
        Light mode
      </button>
    </div>

    <article class="essay">
      <h1>hi, i'm Naman</h1>

      <p>I’m 15 and I am an engineer.</p>

      <p>I want to figure out how to ask great questions.</p>

      <p>I&apos;ve dabbled across most realms of building things.</p>

      <p>
        My long-term goal is to build tech that reduces humanity&apos;s existential debt
        <span class="tooltip-wrap">
          <button class="tooltip-trigger" type="button" aria-describedby="existential-debt-tip">
            ?
          </button>
          <span class="tooltip" id="existential-debt-tip" role="tooltip">
            My shorthand for the preventable long-term risks, fragility, and lost future
            potential humanity keeps handing to itself.
          </span>
        </span>
        .
      </p>

      <p>
        current interests: ambient AI, mech interp, latent a2a protocols, economics,
        superforcasting, nihilism, existential lit/phil, fire technology, aerospace,
        inference-time structures
      </p>

      <h2>Some things I think are important:</h2>
      <ul class="plain-list">
        <li>thinking ruthlessly independently</li>
        <li>coming up with elegant ideas</li>
        <li>convincing people what you believe is right</li>
        <li>sidequesting on occasion</li>
        <li>doing things that I think about when I am not doing them</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        my theory is that if I get better at reflecting on how I implement advice and identify
        what I am bad at, at repeat fast enough, I can recursively improve
      </p>

      <div class="link-grid" aria-label="Site sections">
        <a class="page-card" href="/about">
          <span class="page-card-kicker">separate page</span>
          <strong class="page-card-title">About</strong>
          <span class="page-card-copy">
            notes, beliefs, favorite theorems, and the stuff that used to live in the about section.
          </span>
        </a>

        <a class="page-card" href="/things-ive-done">
          <span class="page-card-kicker">separate page</span>
          <strong class="page-card-title">Things I&apos;ve Done</strong>
          <span class="page-card-copy">
            awards, projects, competition results, and technical work I&apos;m proud of.
          </span>
        </a>

        <a class="page-card" href="/reading">
          <span class="page-card-kicker">separate page</span>
          <strong class="page-card-title">Reading</strong>
          <span class="page-card-copy">
            favorite writing, morsels of wisdom, and things I keep reading outside my lane.
          </span>
        </a>
      </div>

      <p>Breakfast: billions of tokens.</p>
    </article>

    <a
      class="corner-link"
      href="https://github.com/coder-2011"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noreferrer"
    >
      github.com/coder-2011
    </a>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
